<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="468" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,1479,1973]" pageId="15" pageNumber="468">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1660,1685]" pageId="15" pageNumber="468">Remarks.</emphasis>
The Turkish specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kovalev" authorityYear="1978" box="[624,786,1660,1685]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Platypalpus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="468" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="annulitarsis">
<emphasis box="[624,786,1660,1685]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="468">P. annulitarsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have a yellow postpedicel and abdomen and is identified in the key by 
<bibRefCitation box="[314,627,1695,1720]" pageId="15" pageNumber="468" refId="ref22669" refString="Grootaert, P. &amp; Chvala, M. (1992) Monograph of the genus Platypalpus (Diptera: Empidoidea, Hybotidae) of the Mediterranean region and the Canary Islands. Acta Universitatis Carolinae-Biologica, 36, 3 - 226." type="journal article">Grootaert &amp; Chvála (1992)</bibRefCitation>
as 
<taxonomicName authority="(Becker, 1910)" authorityName="Becker" authorityYear="1910" baseAuthorityName="Becker" baseAuthorityYear="1910" box="[669,988,1695,1720]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Platypalpus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="468" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="villeneuvi">
<emphasis box="[669,809,1695,1720]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="468">P. villeneuvi</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation box="[826,980,1695,1720]" pageId="15" pageNumber="468" refId="ref21726" refString="Becker, T. (1910) Orthorrhapha Brachycera; Cyclorrhapha Holometopa. In: Becker, T., Kuntze, A., Schnabl, J. &amp; Villeneuve, E., Dipterologische Sammelreise nach Korsika (Dipt.). Deutsche Entomologische Zeitrschrift, 6, 635 - 665." type="journal article">Becker, 1910</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. The latter species was redescribed by 
<bibRefCitation box="[151,454,1732,1757]" pageId="15" pageNumber="468" refId="ref22669" refString="Grootaert, P. &amp; Chvala, M. (1992) Monograph of the genus Platypalpus (Diptera: Empidoidea, Hybotidae) of the Mediterranean region and the Canary Islands. Acta Universitatis Carolinae-Biologica, 36, 3 - 226." type="journal article">Grootaert &amp; Chvála (1992)</bibRefCitation>
on the basis of a female 
<typeStatus box="[730,828,1732,1757]" pageId="15" pageNumber="468">holotype</typeStatus>
from 
<collectingRegion box="[896,985,1732,1757]" country="France" name="Corse" pageId="15" pageNumber="468">
<collectingCountry box="[896,985,1732,1757]" name="France" pageId="15" pageNumber="468">Corsica</collectingCountry>
</collectingRegion>
. Males remain unknown and therefore it is impossible to formally synonymize both species unless additional material from the 
<typeStatus box="[1171,1219,1768,1792]" pageId="15" pageNumber="468">type</typeStatus>
locality, including males are collected. Turkish specimens agree in all details with the original description of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Kovalev 1978)" authorityName="Kovalev" authorityYear="1978" baseAuthorityName="Kovalev" baseAuthorityYear="1978" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Platypalpus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="468" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anulitarsis">
<emphasis box="[1175,1324,1804,1829]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="468">P. anulitarsis</emphasis>
(Kovalev 1978)
</taxonomicName>
(including details of the male genitalia, midtibial spur, etc.) except size, colour of abdomen and shape and colour of antenna. These are the first records for 
<collectingCountry box="[698,780,1876,1901]" name="Turkey" pageId="15" pageNumber="468">Turkey</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,1479,1973]" pageId="15" pageNumber="468">
For clarity, all differences between specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[819,895,1912,1935]" name="France" pageId="15" pageNumber="468">France</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[961,1042,1911,1936]" name="Turkey" pageId="15" pageNumber="468">Turkey</collectingCountry>
, redescription of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Becker" baseAuthorityYear="1910" box="[1253,1395,1911,1936]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Platypalpus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="468" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="villeneuvi">
<emphasis box="[1253,1395,1911,1936]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="468">P. villeneuvi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation box="[151,453,1948,1973]" pageId="15" pageNumber="468" refId="ref22669" refString="Grootaert, P. &amp; Chvala, M. (1992) Monograph of the genus Platypalpus (Diptera: Empidoidea, Hybotidae) of the Mediterranean region and the Canary Islands. Acta Universitatis Carolinae-Biologica, 36, 3 - 226." type="journal article">Grootaert &amp; Chvála (1992)</bibRefCitation>
and the original description (Kovalev 1978) of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Kovalev" baseAuthorityYear="1978" box="[982,1129,1948,1973]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Platypalpus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="468" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anulitarsis">
<emphasis box="[982,1129,1948,1973]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="468">P. anulitarsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are summarized in 
<tableCitation box="[1347,1430,1948,1973]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="16.[151,239,152,175]" captionText="TABLE 1. Differences between P.villeneuvi (only female known) and P.annulitarsis from various locations." pageId="15" pageNumber="468">Table 1</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
